The paper discusses the use of hierarchical feedforward networks for object categorization tasks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a novel pooling layer and discusses its impact on network performance, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the importance of selective invariance in pattern recognition, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
